as risk his life and freedom by returning to England? And why did he bring the now-missing young boy with him? Several nervous Londoners had reason to fear that Nicholas Hayes had returned to kill them. One of them might have decided to kill him first"--Provided by publisher. 0aSaint Cyr, Sebastian (Fictitious character)vFiction. 0aMurderxInvestigationvFiction. 0aNobilityxCrimes againstvFiction. 0aGreat BritainxHistoryyGeorge III, 1760-1820vFiction. 0aLarge type books. 7aMystery fiction.2gsafd 7aDetective and mystery fiction.2lcgft 7aHistorical fiction.2lcgft1 aHarris, C. S.tSebastian St. Cyr mystery series.  c(OCoLC)1137837691  c4486d4486